CDFglobalAttributes.Description: ICON EUV L2.6 derived daytime ionosphere products
CDFglobalAttributes.LINK_TEXT: ICON EUV Retrieved Dayside Ionosphere Products
CDFglobalAttributes.Logical_source_description: ICON EUV derived ionospheric data products
CDFglobalAttributes.TEXT: ICON explores the boundary between Earth and space (the ionosphere) to understand the physical connection between our world and the immediate space environment around us. Visit https://icon.ssl.berkeley.edu for more details.
CDFglobalAttributes.TITLE: ICON EUV Daytime Ionosphere Products L2.6

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Binary Coded Integer Describing the Activity Category of EUV
VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Flag for activity status of the EUV instrument, as defined in the Ephemeris Definition Document.

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Depend_1 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Altitude corresponding to the retrieved quantities, in WGS84

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Display_Type FieldNam FillVal Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Name of the file containing the EUV ancillary data.

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Value of the daily Ap index used in the retrieval.

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Solar scattering counts present in the image, distinct from the regular background, and is evaluated but not removed from the data before L2 processing. This occurs seasonally with the most significant effect visible when the spacecraft is near the dawn-dusk terminators.

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Local Earth radius at retrieval location, from WGS

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: The daily F10.7 values used in the retrieval, in solar flux units. The data are obtained directly from The Solar Radio Monitoring Program through Natural Resources Canada (https://www.spaceweather.gc.ca/solarflux/sx-en.php).

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Custom F10.7a value used in the retrieval, in solar flux units. This value is constructed at the ICON Science Data Center and is meant to provide a timely approximation to the 81-day F10.7a average used in atmospheric models, but is centered on a date 33 days prior to the ICON measurement, specifically encompassing F10.7 data from 73 days prior to 7 days after the measurement.

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Quality flag associated with the L2 retrieval and/or L1 data. 0 = No issues reported,  1 = Moderate issue(s) identified, use results with caution, 2 = Severe issue(s) identified, recommend not using data product for this profile. See the ICON_L26_Flag_Details variable for additional information for the reported causes on any non-zero values

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Display_Type FieldNam FillVal Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Provides additional detail on issues in the retrieval that resulted in a data quality flag of seriousness level 1 (moderate) or 2 (severe), as contained in the ICON_L26_Flag variable.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Height of F2 Layer from Retrieval
VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Height of the peak electron density of the F2 layer from retrieval, in WGS. The relationship between retrieved O+ and electron densities is inferred using IRI2007.

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Depend_1 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: *Diagnostic* Tangent altitudes corresponding to the input data, in WGS84

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Depend_1 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: *Diagnostic* Covariance of the observed Radiance in the 61.7 nm wavelength channel

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Depend_1 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: *Diagnostic* Covariance of the observed Radiance in the 83.4 nm wavelength channel

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Display_Type FieldNam FillVal Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Name of the EUV L1 file containing the input data.

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Depend_1 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: *Diagnostic* Observed Radiance in the 61.7 nm wavelength channel

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Depend_1 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: *Diagnostic* Observed Radiance in the 83.4 nm wavelength channel

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Geodetic latitude at retrieval location, referenced at 300 km altitude, in WGS

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Local solar time at retrieval location

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Geodetic longitude at retrieval location, referenced at 300 km altitude, in WGS

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Quasi-dipole magnetic latitude at retrieval location, referenced at 300 km, calculated using the fast implementation developed by Emmert et al. (2010, doi:10.1029/2010JA015326) and the Python wrapper apexpy (https://github.com/aburrell/apexpy/).

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Quasi-dipole magnetic longitude at retrieval location, referenced at 300 km, calculated using the fast implementation developed by Emmert et al. (2010, doi:10.1029/2010JA015326) and the Python wrapper apexpy (https://github.com/aburrell/apexpy/).

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Depend_1 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: *Diagnostic* A value of 1 shows which forward model parameters are set to change during the retrieval, where the parameters are in order: Rz12 multiplier, ig12 multiplier, IRI F107 multiplier, density scalar, j0 multiplier

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Depend_1 Depend_2 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: *Diagnostic* Covariance matrix of the model parameters from the retrieval.

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Depend_1 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: *Diagnostic* Lower limit of the parameters used in the forward model, which are in order: Rz12 multiplier, ig12 multiplier, IRI F107 multiplier, density scalar, j0 multiplier

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Depend_1 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: *Diagnostic* Parameters used in the forwared model, which are in order: Rz12 multiplier, ig12 multiplier, IRI F107 multiplier, density scalar, j0 multiplier

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Depend_1 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: *Diagnostic* Initial values of the parameters used in the forward model, which are in order: Rz12 multiplier, ig12 multiplier, IRI F107 multiplier, density scalar, j0 multiplier

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Depend_1 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: *Diagnostic* Upper limit of the parameters used in the forward model, which are in order: Rz12 multiplier, ig12 multiplier, IRI F107 multiplier, density scalar, j0 multiplier
